The paper deals with the problem of computing maximin share allocations, which is a problem in fair division. This falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also involves the use of approximation algorithms and probabilistic analysis, which are techniques commonly used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of matchings in bipartite graphs, which is a topic in both algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of fair division, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
